GFG : Reverse a string


Reverse a String in Java
Last Updated : 03 Jan, 2025
In Java, reversing a string means reordering the string characters from the last to the first position. There are multiple ways to reverse a string, each with its advantages.

Example:

The for loop is a simple, straightforward approach to reverse a string in Java that offers full control over the reversal process without relying on additional classes.



// Java Program to Reverse a String
// Using for loop
import java.io.*;
import java.util.Scanner;

class GFG {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
      
        String s = "Geeks"; 
        String r = "";
        char ch;

        for (int i = 0; i < s.length(); i++) {
              
              // extracts each character
            ch = s.charAt(i);
          
              // adds each character in
            // front of the existing string
            r = ch + r; 
        }
      
        System.out.println(r);
    }
}
